  "texts": [
    "These principles include strategies such as sense-making, elaboration, self-explanation, partial task solution, and the use of metacognitive and motivational scaffolds.",
    "These strategies are usually employed as part of cognitively activating activities (see Section II B).",
    "The third part consists of a Refinement, which includes aspects that are known to compromise the learning effectiveness of the considered theoretical principles in the second part.",
    "Here, we included the restriction \"without giving the correct answer\".",
    "This restriction is motivated by prior research indicating that providing elaborated feedback in combination with the correct answer leads to a low efficiency of the feedback (Kulhavy et al., 1985; Phye & Bender, 1989) and may lead to superficial learning (Schimmel, 1988)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
